modules.description: Checks for discrepancies between OCaml external declarations and their C implementations by analyzing .ml and .cmt files. Extracts argument counts from OCaml signatures and compares them against C function definitions. Generates C header files to ensure consistency in stubs and their corresponding C code.

Provides functions to extract and convert C type information from OCaml's internal representation, specifically mapping native arguments to C type strings. It processes OCaml interface files (`.cmt`/`.cmti`) to iterate over primitive definitions and their type expressions. Used to safely load and analyze OCaml primitives for interoperability with C code.
